arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyComplete(S_BOSS_LEVEL_AREA)
	
	-- [DB] Finish collapsing scaffolding
	local idScaffold = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_Scaffold")[1]
	local idRope = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_ExitPortal")[1]
	
	-- This is the exit
	Hydra.ActorEnable(idRope)
end

function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	-- Player line on first demon killed in tower
	Hydra.Wait(0.5)
	if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idActorKiller) then
		Hydra.ActorPlayConversation(convPlayerDemonKill, idActorKiller)
	end
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, sWorldName)
	-- When entering Sanctuary,
	Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_POWER_EXP_ADJUSTER, "PATH_TO_DUNGEON", idActorPlayer) -- add world buff
	Hydra.BuffRemove(S_POWER_EXP_ADJUSTER, "DUNGEON", idActorPlayer) -- remove dungeon buff 
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, sWorldName)
	-- When entering the dungeon
	Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_POWER_EXP_ADJUSTER, "DUNGEON", idActorPlayer) -- add dungeon buff
	Hydra.BuffRemove(S_POWER_EXP_ADJUSTER, "PATH_TO_DUNGEON", idActorPlayer) -- remove world buff 
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)
	-- Adding brief wait to allow the SFX of the corpse to play
	-- without being stomped by the objective complete sfx
	Hydra.Wait(1)
	
	-- Start the boss music
	--Hydra.MusicOverride("CSD_Frac_Prologue_AbandonedTower", S_BOSS_MUSIC)
	
	-- Find the Trigger
	local idTrigger = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_BossTrigger")[1]
	
	-- Find the boss
	local idBoss = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(idTrigger, "BOSS")[1]
	
	Hydra.ActorEnable(idBoss)
	Hydra.ActorSetAILocalVariable(idBoss, "INTRO", 1);
	Hydra.ActorTriggerPowerAtFeet(idBoss, BOSS_INTRO_POWER);
	
	-- Evade Tutorial
	local tPlayers = Hydra.QuestGetParticipants()
	for i = 1, #tPlayers do
		Hydra.ShowTutorial("Evade", tPlayers[i])
	end
	
	-- Start the boss fight
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyQueueStart(S_BOSS_LEVEL_AREA)
	
	-- [ZH] Delete the Trigger so it doesn't re-trigger during fight failure.
	Hydra.ActorKill(idTrigger)
	
	-- [DB] Wait to sync with boss landing before collapsing scaffolding
	Hydra.Wait(0)
	local idScaffold = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_Scaffold")[1]
	local idScaffoldNoRope = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_Scaffold_NoRope")[1]
	Hydra.QActorAnimAndNewIdle(idScaffold, ANIM_COLLAPSE_01, ANIM_COLLAPSE_IDLE_01)
	Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idActorGizmo, S_VFX_SHAKE_AND_DUST)
	Hydra.QActorAnimAndNewIdle(idScaffold, ANIM_COLLAPSE_02, ANIM_COLLAPSE_IDLE_02)
	Hydra.ActorSetIdleAnim(idScaffoldNoRope, ANIM_COLLAPSE_IDLE_02)
end

function Start(idActor, idActorDetector)
	-- Find the boss linked to the trigger.
	local idBoss = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(idActorDetector, "BOSS")[1]
	
	Hydra.ActorEnable(idBoss)
	
	-- Start the boss fight
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyQueueStart(S_BOSS_LEVEL_AREA)
	
	-- [ZH] Delete the Trigger so it doesn't re-trigger during fight failure.
	Hydra.ActorKill(idActorDetector)
	
	-- Start the boss music
	--Hydra.MusicOverride("CSD_Frac_Prologue_AbandonedTower", S_BOSS_MUSIC)
	
	
end

arQuestPhases.szOnEnterScript:
-- Clear and Reset Boss Music on Retry/Fail
Hydra.ClearMusicOverride("CSD_Frac_Prologue_AbandonedTower")

-- Reset the boss music
Hydra.ClearMusicOverride("CSD_Frac_Prologue_AbandonedTower")

--Hide switch scaffold rope
local idScaffold = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_Scaffold")[1]
local idScaffoldNoRope = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("Prologue_Tower_Scaffold_NoRope")[1]
Hydra.ActorEnable(idScaffoldNoRope)
Hydra.ActorDisable(idScaffold)

szOnStartupScript:
-- Override weather
S_WORLD_SANCTUARY = Hydra.ReferenceWorld("Sanctuary_Eastern_Continent")
S_WEATHER_PROLOGUE = Hydra.ReferenceWeather("weather_FracturedPeaks_prologue")
Hydra.WeatherOverride(S_WORLD_SANCTUARY, S_WEATHER_PROLOGUE)
Hydra.TimeOfDaySetOverride(S_WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.0)

-- Deactivate dungeon portal until gate is opened
-- to help with controllers selecting overlapping gizmos
Hydra.ActorDisable(actorRuinsPortal)

--Boss Music Reference

S_BOSS_MUSIC = Hydra.ReferenceMusic("Music_WorldBoss_TreasureBeast_Spawn")

-- Used to adjust how much exp players are getting from monster kills
S_POWER_EXP_ADJUSTER = Hydra.ReferencePower("QST_Prologue_Experience_Adjuster");
